# Codexia Security Model

## Purpose

Codexia modifies software systems.

The architecture must prioritise safe execution, controlled changes, and developer trust.


## Security Principles


## Controlled File Access

File operations should:

- validate paths
- prevent unsafe traversal
- restrict access scope


## Patch-First Changes

Codexia should not blindly overwrite files.

Preferred workflow:

Plan

↓

Generate Patch

↓

Validate Patch

↓

Apply Change

↓

Verify Result


## Secret Protection

The system must avoid exposing:

- environment variables
- API keys
- credentials
- private configuration


## Observable Actions

All autonomous actions should provide:

- what changed
- why it changed
- which files were affected


## Recovery

Failed operations should support:

- rollback
- repair planning
- clear failure reporting